<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 07 at 4:21AM EST  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...SNOW WILL IMPACT THE EARLY MORNING COMMUTE IN THE BUFFALO METRO
AREA...
There will be a burst of snow which will impact early portions of
the morning commute in Erie and Niagara counties, which includes
Niagara Falls and the Buffalo metro area. The heaviest snow will
be through 6 a.m. with snowfall rates up to an inch an hour and
visibility as low as a half mile at times. This will produce a
total of 2 to 3 inches of snow, resulting in slick roadways and
poor visibility.
The snow will begin to taper off between 6 a.m. and 7 a.m. with
most of the accumulating snow expected to be done by 8 a.m.
Surface temperatures will be near or slightly above freezing
during this time.</description>
